author = "R.J. Gould",
abstract = "The stopping power of a plasma for fast electrons and positrons is calculated. First the classical limit is considered where β = ν/c ⪡ α is the fine structure constant. Then the nonrelativistic Born-approximation formulas are derived; this domain corresponds to α ⪡ β ⪡ 1. Finally the general case of relativistic electrons and positrons is treated; in the relativistic case the scattering cross sections of Møller (electron-electron) and Bhabha (positron-electron) are used in the calculation. In all three energy domains the problem is broken up into cases of small and large momentum transfers (ℏq). For large q, scattering off individual plasma electrons is considered, while in the limit of very small q for the quantum-mechanical domain, excitation of quantized plasma oscillations contributes to dE/dx; in the classical limit for small q (or large impact parameter), the polarizability of the plasma provides the effective cutoff. The formulas for the stopping power differ slightly from those for a heavy ion going through a plasma because (i) there are exchange effects and (ii) the fast electrons and positrons can lose a large fraction of their energy in one scattering off a plasma electron."
}

